column22: Overexpression of BACH decreased the amount of NRF2 localization to the NQO1 gene ARE region via CHIP competition assay
Overexpression of Nrf2 decreased the amount of BACH1 localization to the NQO1 gene ARE region via CHIP competition assay
overexpression of both keap1 and p62 can cause aggregation of Nrf2

Fractionation was combined with mass spectrometry from five diverse animal species to predict co-complex protein interactions conserved across metazoa using an integrative computational scoring procedure along with an SVM approach. The significant data set of 16655 PPI, was derived from a set of more than 1M interactions by examining a ROC curve of predicted interactions against reference annotated complexes at a 67.5% cumulative precision.

This human reference interactome (HuRI) was generated by performing nine two-hybrid screens with the high confidence interactions determined by pairwise verification by quadruplicate retesting and sequence confirmation. This HI-III-20 dataset contains over 52,000 PPIs involving more than 8,000 proteins.
